(82, 1, '{\"_token\":\"cwEP1W5e1VEpeOuMa1L45Q2FGRb4gvGwdFzIuQJ6\",\"name\":\"Connie McCamey\",\"subject\":\"Question about your rug safety\",\"email\":\"connie_anne@hotmail.com\",\"phone\":\"2092078576\",\"company\":\"None\",\"city\":\"Angels Camp\",\"state\":\"CA\",\"message\":\"We purchased a LR home rug and it is constantly \\u201cshedding\\u201d a white powdery substance. This powder covers the floor under the rug and often can be seen on the edges of the rug too. My son has developed some sort of allergy that we can not figure out and we are wondering if it could be related to whatever the white power is. I\\u2019m am sure it gets in the air when I vacuum and sweep. What is the powder made of? Have other people reported something similar?\"}', '2022-11-21 07:20:34', '2022-11-21 07:20:34', NULL),
